# Git Initialization Guide & Commands

# 1. Initialize local Git repository
git init
git branch -M main

# 2. Link your local repository to GitHub/GitLab
# (Replace '<your-repository-url>' with your actual repository URL)
# git remote add origin <your-repository-url>

# 3. Stage and commit all existing project files
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit - Hotel Booking System project setup"

# 4. Push your project code to the main branch
# git push -u origin main

# 5. Create a new branch and push your features
# git checkout -b <branch_name>
# git add .
# git commit -m "Describe your changes"
# git push -u origin <branch_name>
